Git has 3 states:
1) modified :   whenever we have a file which is not tracked then its in a modified state.
2) staged   : git add <filename>  : after this command the file is now in staged state and is getting tracked.
3) commit   : git commit <filename> : commit means the file is now safely stored in local database.




sudo install apt git
